Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 12:20:41 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] =?UTF-8?q?T-Display=20P4:=20fix=20serial=20client=20A?=
 =?UTF-8?q?PI=20=E2=80=94=20polling=20console,=20no=20hosted=20BLE?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two stacked bugs kept the protobuf API from answering on UART0/COM6:

1. SERIAL_HAS_ON_RECEIVE (esp32-common) parks SerialConsole on INT32_MAX
   waiting for HardwareSerial::onReceive, which never fires on this P4
   core — logs streamed out but the console never read a byte. Unflag it
   so the console polls (250ms idle / 5ms active), same as NRF52/RP2040.

2. The stock LilyGo C6 firmware (ESP-AT) passes SDIO card init but never
   completes the esp_hosted handshake; after the 10s timeout and a failed
   slave reset the hosted driver reboots the host every ~19s
   (os_wrapper_esp: Restarting host), killing any client mid-config.
   Exclude Bluetooth until the C6 is reflashed with the esp_hosted
   network_adapter slave (Milestone B).

Verified: meshtastic python client connects on COM6, full config dump
through config_complete_id, nodedb download OK.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/platformio.ini | 13 +++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+)

diff --git a/variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/platformio.ini b/variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/platformio.ini
index 47708b1af..bf437a23d 100644
--- a/variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/platformio.ini
+++ b/variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/platformio.ini
@@ -22,6 +22,13 @@ build_src_filter =
   ${esp32p4_base.build_src_filter}
   +<../variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4>
 
+; SERIAL_HAS_ON_RECEIVE makes SerialConsole sleep (INT32_MAX) until a
+; HardwareSerial::onReceive callback wakes it. On this board the callback
+; never fires (logs stream out on UART0 but the protobuf API never reads a
+; byte), so drop the flag and let the console poll like NRF52/RP2040 do.
+build_unflags = ${esp32p4_base.build_unflags}
+  -DSERIAL_HAS_ON_RECEIVE
+
 build_flags = ${esp32p4_base.build_flags}
   -Ivariants/esp32p4/t-display-p4
   -DTDISPLAY_P4
@@ -31,6 +38,12 @@ build_flags = ${esp32p4_base.build_flags}
   -DFS_PARTITION_LABEL=\"mesh_fs\"
   -DRADIOLIB_DEBUG_BASIC=1
   -DRADIOLIB_DEBUG_SPI=1
+  ; Milestone A: no BLE. The stock LilyGo C6 firmware (ESP-AT) passes SDIO
+  ; card init but never completes the esp_hosted handshake; after a 10s
+  ; timeout + failed slave reset the hosted driver REBOOTS THE HOST
+  ; ("os_wrapper_esp: Restarting host") every ~19s. Re-enable after the C6
+  ; is reflashed with the esp_hosted network_adapter slave (Milestone B).
+  -DMESHTASTIC_EXCLUDE_BLUETOOTH=1
 
 ; The ng-io-expander fork's idf_component.yml has a broken P4-conditional rule
 ; requesting espressif/cbor ^2.0.12 (no such version exists; cbor is only used
